<quiz><question number="17">
        <prompt>What was the significance of the "pool" system in railroad operations?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Divided railroad profits among competing lines</option>
            <option letter="b">Created new railway construction methods</option>
            <option letter="c">Improved passenger service</option>
            <option letter="d">Regulated ticket prices</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Railroad pools were agreements between competing railroads to divide business in a territory and share profits, reducing competition and maintaining high rates.</explanation>
    </question>
