        <prompt>How did the growth of mail-order catalogs affect rural America?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Connected rural consumers to urban markets</option>
            <option letter="b">Reduced retail business</option>
            <option letter="c">Increased local manufacturing</option>
            <option letter="d">Promoted urbanization</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Mail-order catalogs like Montgomery Ward and Sears Roebuck connected rural consumers to urban markets, revolutionizing rural retail and consumption patterns.</explanation>
